{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Vto7gPHSsvLQErYdwr5ZXA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"CockroachDB is running in `--insecure` mode, so the DB Console (port 8080) is served over plain HTTP (no TLS on the backend). The task says \"TLS required\" for the ingress, meaning I need to set up TLS termination at the ingress level.\n\nFor the DB Console:\n- Backend: `crdb-cluster-public:8080` (HTTP)\n- Frontend (ingress): `https://crdb-ui.example.com` (HTTPS with TLS termination at ingress)\n\nI need to:\n1. Create a self-signed TLS certificate for `crdb-ui.example.com` and store it as a Kubernetes secret\n2. Create an Ingress resource with TLS enabled using that secret, the nginx ingress class, and the backend service on port 8080\n\nFor the SQL TCP proxy, I'll need to configure the ingress-nginx controller to handle raw TCP traffic on port 26257 by creating a configmap that maps that port to the CockroachDB service, then patching the controller deployment and service to expose and use it.\n\nLet me first check if a `tcp-services` configmap already exists in the ingress-nginx namespace.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1170,"cache_read_input_tokens":31522,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1170},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7de5e166-7b10-4a45-8a8d-8611f2287267","uuid":"aec3d78b-684f-49e6-b968-9538f1bfc170","request_id":"req_011CcasQsiHMXYEZXXvXiwTz"}
